counts = Counter(letters)

odd_chars = [char for char, count in counts.items() if count % 2 != 0]

middle_char = ''
if len(odd_chars) > 0:
    middle_char = odd_chars[0]
    counts[middle_char] -= 1
    if counts[middle_char] == 0:
      del counts[middle_char]

first_half = ''
for char in sorted(counts.keys()):
    first_half += char * (counts[char] // 2)

second_half = first_half[::-1]

palindrome = first_half + middle_char + second_half

print(palindrome)
